# 📝 Homework: Build a Mini Website – "My Learning Library"

## 📌 Goal:
Create a simple multi-page website that showcases **Users**, **Subjects**, and **Books** using **HTML and CSS only**. The final product should help you deeply understand:

- HTML structure and elements
- CSS styling, selectors, pseudo-classes/elements
- Style cascading and file organization

---

## 🧱 Pages to Create

Create **3 HTML pages**:

1. `index.html` – Homepage that introduces the website
2. `users.html` – List of users with details
3. `library.html` – List of subjects and books under each subject

---

## 🎯 Requirements

### 1. HTML Elements (Use at least once)

Use the following tags where appropriate across your pages:

`html`, `body`, `head`, `header`, `footer`, `a`, `area`, `article`, `audio`
`code`, `div`, `embed`, `form`, `iframe`, `h1` → `h6`, `b`, `br`, `button`, `canvas`
`img`, `input`, `label`, `li`, `link`, `menu`, `ol`, `select`, `option`
`strong`, `table`, `th`, `td`, `tr`, `u`, `ul`, `video`
`style`, `script` (script can be empty placeholder for now)

> 💡 **Tip:** You can use `audio`, `video`, or `iframe` to embed content like YouTube or sample mp3/video files.

---

### 2. HTML Attributes

Use:
- `id`, `class`
- Common attributes like: `href`, `src`, `alt`, `type`, `name`, `value`, `target`, etc.

---

### 3. CSS Topics to Cover

#### ✅ CSS Syntax & Selectors

Use:
- **Internal**, **inline**, and **external** CSS
- CSS Selectors:
  - `.class`, `#id`
  - `element`, `element element`, `element > element`
  - `[attribute]`, `[attribute=value]`, `[attribute^=value]`, `[attribute*=value]`

#### ✅ CSS Properties

Use:
- `background`, `border`, `color`, `cursor`, `display`, `flex`
- `font-family`, `font-size`, `font-weight`, `font-style`, `@font-face`
- `width`, `height`, `margin`, `padding`, `position`, `top`, `left`, `float`
- `line-height`, `list-style`, `opacity`, `overflow`
- `animation` *(optional: simple keyframe)*

#### ✅ Pseudo Classes & Elements

Use at least **5** of the following:
- `:hover`, `:focus`, `:checked`, `:first-child`, `:last-child`
- `::before`, `::after`, `:nth-child(n)`, `:not(selector)`

---

## 📂 Suggested Folder Structure

```text
/my-learning-library
│
├── index.html
├── users.html
├── library.html
├── styles/
│   └── main.css
└── assets/
    ├── images/
    └── media/
